language Essence 1.3

given n: int(1..)
given k: int(1..)
given edges: set of set (size 2) of int(1..n)
find colouring: matrix indexed by [int(1..n), int(1..k)] of int(0..1)
such that
    and([sum([colouring[vertex, colour] | colour : int(1..k)]) = 1 | vertex : int(1..n)]),
    and([and([{v1, v2} in edges -> and([colouring[v1, colour] + colouring[v2, colour] <= 1 | colour : int(1..k)])
                  | v2 : int(v1 + 1..n)])
             | v1 : int(1..n)])

